10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy&#39;&gt;Sorry, no docu=
ment or report, but I&#8217;m
happy to answer your questions.&nbsp; One thi=
ng to remember though is that this
is a modified heritrix crawler.&nbsp; We=
 decoupled the content persistence from
the fetching.&nbsp; So when I say 4=
 machines, that&#8217;s 4 machines just
doing fetching and managing of the =
crawler queue&#8217;s.&nbsp; There was a
fifth machine (could be a movie ti=
tle, &#8220;The Fifth Machine&#8221; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font
size=3D2 color=3Dn=
avy face=3DWingdings&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:
Wingdings=
;color:navy&#39;&gt;J&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D2 color=3Dnavy face=3DArial&gt;&lt;span
=
style=3D&#39;font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;color:navy&#39;&gt;) that handled all =
the
content store.&nbsp; We have a custom writer that streams the content t=
o the remote
persistence layer.&nbsp; The persistence layer compresses the =
content and
writes it to disk.&nbsp; Internally we have a gigabit network c=
onnecting the
servers.&nbsp; The io on each server is pretty modest, just a=
 big 750gb SATA
drive for the content and a smaller drive for the o/s.&nbsp=
; The o/s runs in
its own partition.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

